values:
Wow. I was just realizing how I never seem to post on this anymore. Its been almost a month since I've even gone to lj. That's just sad.&nbsp; 

I was wondering... can certain relationships mess with other relationships? Can personal issues truly effect *sp* the ones you love? They always say that what you do impacts everyone around you... because they care... but what does it take to understand? Does it really take being in that person's poisition? Do you really have to walk two moons in their moccasins do get it?&nbsp; 

I think I finally understand now. It&nbsp;feels good... almost... I get it now. It can be dark... and scary, I suppose. Depressing, almost, but in a relief-ee sort of way... Its confusing... yet somehow, it all pulls together and makes sense. Right there. Suddenly, it's just there. And there's nothing&nbsp;else about it. No second guessing... no past questions... it's so simple. Just how it feels, you can't control it, though some (in the beginning...) hope that they can.&nbsp; 

Everyone says: "Yeah... Betty died last year from it... but that won't happen to me, I can control it." That's what you think until you really begin to feel that dark abyss that surrounded Betty last year. It begins to drag you under, and there's nothing you can do. Yet somehow, the surreality of it all becomes your buoy. The fact that it is a relief; washing away everything from your body. It floats you back to the top, and somehow, you're alright again.&nbsp; 

Maybe the next time you're feeling sad and lonely, it'll happen again. But maybe that's not such a bad thing.
